OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F434A1775571065
OL,3,CLifeguard warning after teenagers
OL,4,Csaved from powerful rip current
OL,6,FLifeguards said they spent the morning
OL,7,Fwarning beachgoers of strong easterly
OL,8,Fwinds, hazardous currents and a 2-3ft
OL,9,Fswell when they spotted the teenagers
OL,10,Fapproaching the water at one of the
OL,11,Fbeach's most dangerous areas, which
OL,12,Fhas a well-known, fixed rip current.
OL,14,FBefore they could be warned, two
OL,15,Fmembers of the group were quickly
OL,16,Fswept 100 metres out to sea, reaching
OL,17,Fthe offshore marker buoys within
OL,18,Fseconds.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
